  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nIn desktop we use in a couple of places the function `saveConfiguration` https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/src/app_service/service/node_configuration/service.nim#L82 to update values in the node config, like the log level, waku mode, waku version, etc. This can lead to errors in which the node configuration being saved does not have correct values in case it was modified by status-go by some other function, and we might end up overriding some value we didnt intend to.\r\n\r\nSolving this will require status-go work to implement new API methods to replace the invocations to saveConfiguration. The flow for these functions should be:\r\n\r\n1. Load the current NodeConfig\r\n2. Modify the NodeConfig setting... (i.e. if we want to switch the log level,  we'd set `config.LogLevel = value`\r\n3. Save the NodeConfig\r\n4. Return the updated node config so status-desktop can update its own state (not sure about this step).",
